abstract: Bond markets sold off aggressively, pushing the 10-year Treasury yield back up to 2.96 percent, near where it was when the Fed first suggested its policy to push down interest rates.
snippet: Bond markets sold off aggressively, pushing the 10-year Treasury yield back up to 2.96 percent, near where it was when the Fed first suggested its policy to push down interest rates.
lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve’s much-anticipated announcement this month that it was intervening in financial markets was intended to push down interest rates to get the economy moving again.

headline.main: Bond Sell-Off in Spite of Intervention by Fed Puzzles Traders and Analysts
headline.print_headline: Bond Sell-Off in Spite of Intervention By Fed Puzzles Traders and Analysts

byline.original: By Graham Bowley and Christine Hauser
